name: ReportRequest
description:
Request message for the Report method.

Generated from protobuf message google.api.servicecontrol.v1.ReportRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.service_name
params.description: The service name as specified in its service configuration. For example, "pubsub.googleapis.com". See google.api.Service for the definition of a service name.

params.name: data.operations
params.description: Operations to be reported. Typically the service should report one operation per request. Putting multiple operations into a single request is allowed, but should be used only when multiple operations are natually available at the time of the report. There is no limit on the number of operations in the same ReportRequest, however the ReportRequest size should be no larger than 1MB. See [ReportResponse.report_errors][google.api.servicecontrol.v1.ReportResponse.report_errors] for partial failure behavior.

params.name: data.service_config_id
params.description: Specifies which version of service config should be used to process the request. If unspecified or no matching version can be found, the latest one will be used.
